The paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms, specifically support vector machines, for the diagnosis of coronary heart disease. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves preprocessing of data, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV) or computational engineering (cs.CE). Finally, the use of performance parameters such as recall, precision, and F-measure suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE).
